{
  "stem": "5758.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I went to his home, his house downstairs in the cellar, and we exchanged stamps.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he was always-- whenever we talked somehow or other about politics, he was very left wing-- seemed to be left wing.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] he-- I believe he supported the Socialist Party, because I myself, was somehow left wing-inclined when I was a student.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, I was a member of the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That is the association of the socialist students.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was never any antisemitic remarks from him or-- he was always left wing, as far as I was concerned.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On the day after the invasion, the 11th of March-- actually, this was my brother's birthday, Eric-- he came up with an insignia of the Nazi Party, and he had a swastika band.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when we passed each other in the building, he said, well, what do you-- what-- what can I do?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's all he said.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What-- what can I do?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he more or less indicated he was forced to do to show his pro-German attitude.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Otherwise-- [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] well, this is an instance.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "How did that-- did that then affect his relationship with you?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, what happened to your relationship with him?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we did not anymore-- we did not anymore exchange stamps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There's one instance-- [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Germans entered Austria in March.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And things were extremely, extremely difficult for Jews because the-- the law, Nuremberg laws, et cetera, were already in-- in-- in Austria-- applied for Austria also.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Nazis, the Austrian Nazis, were tremendously-- it was tremendously anti-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
